
[1]eloquent

   EL'OQUENT, a. Having the power of oratory; speaking with fluency,
   propriety, elegance and animation; as an eloquent orator; an eloquent
   preacher.

   1. Composed with elegance and spirit; elegant and animated; adapted to
   please, affect and persuade; as an eloquent address; an eloquent
   petition or remonstrance; an eloquent history.
